A data set containing measurements of 30 subject on a whole host of activities has been provided for 30 subjects 
Data for the x and y measurememts for training and tests sets are read in.
The table for all the measure names are read in and used as column names.
The features are filtered for only the means and the standard deviations 
Columns of the activities and the subjects are combined with the data.
By using dmelt and d cast , the data are reformed to provide a list of subjects and their mean of 6 activity measures 
all below each other per subject (one line per subject ) . 
Only the means and standard deviations of the measures are provided for the axial measurements.